<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-88-0673 </DOCNO><TEXT>The producers of liquefied petroleum gases (LPG) argue for deregulationof wholesale prices on the grounds that it is more equitable, in thenational interest, and is a more efficient way to allocate resources.Price regulations and other intervention by the government make it difficultfor producers and distributors to deal fairly with each other. Regulationalso dampens incentives to encourage domestic market growth and distortsthe market for alternative fuels. The author refutes arguments againsta free market, and concludes that contract negotiation would be moreeffective. 1 figure.</TEXT></DOC>